        <h5>eToro: The Social Platform</h5>
        <p>eToro pioneered social trading - the idea that following successful traders is easier than learning to trade yourself. Their platform is designed around community, copying, and accessibility. You don't need to learn technical analysis; just find traders with good track records and copy them. They're a "let experts fish for you" platform.</p>

        <h5>Which Philosophy Suits You?</h5>
        <p>If you're committed to learning trading as a skill, building your own strategies, and potentially trading professionally someday - AvaTrade's approach serves you better. The knowledge transfers. If you're a busy professional who wants market exposure without dedicating hours to learning - eToro's copy trading lets you participate without the learning curve.</p>

        <h5>The Hybrid Approach</h5>
        <p>Many traders use both. eToro for passive copy trading (set it and forget it), AvaTrade for active trading where they apply their own analysis. There's no rule saying you can only have one broker account.</p>
